<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7958943>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A–D Labia of Parena spp.: A P. (Crossoglossa) cavipennis (Bates), Beijing. B P. (Parena) latecincta (Bates), Zhejiang. C P. (Bothynoptera) dorsigera (Schaum), Guangxi. D P. (Bothynoptera) tripunctata (Bates), Beijing. E–F Heads of Parena spp. in lateral view: E P. (Bothynoptera) taiwana Hua, Taiwan, suborbital setae present. F P. (Parena) latecincta (Bates), Yunnan, suborbital seta absent. Scale bars = 0.5mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7958943/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7958939>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Antennae and mouthparts of Parena spp. A–D Line drawings of basal three antennomeres, view of lateral surface: A P. (Crossoglossa) cavipennis (Bates). B P. (Bothynoptera) malaisei (Andrewes). C P. (Parena) africana (Alluaud). D P. (Parena) ruficornis sp. n. E Antennomeres 7–11 of P. (Parena) nigrolineata (Chaudoir), showing the sensory pits on dorsal surface. F–G Labrum of P. (Crossoglossa) cavipennis (Bates), Beijing: F dorsal surface. G ventral surface. H Maxilla of P. (Crossoglossa) cavipennis (Bates), Beijing. Scale bars = 0.2mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7958939/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7959031>
    dc:description "FIGURE 46. Parena (Bothynoptera) emarginata sp. n. A Habitus of holotype. B Habitus of paratype. C Mouthparts of holotype. D Labels of holotype. Scale bars = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7959031/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7958941>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Mandibles of Parena spp.: left mandible, dorsum (ld); right mandible, dorsum (rd); left mandible, venter (lv); right mandible, venter (rv). A P. (Crossoglossa) cavipennis (Bates), Shaanxi. B P. (Parena) latecincta (Bates), Zhejiang. C P. (Bothynoptera) dorsigera (Schaum), Guangxi. D P. (Bothynoptera) taiwana Hua, Taiwan. E P. (Bothynoptera) tripunctata (Bates), Beijing. Scale bar = 0.5mm. Abbreviations: rr retinacular ridge of right mandible; vg ventral groove." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7958941/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7958991>
    dc:description "FIGURE 26. Parena (Bothynoptera) heteronycha sp. n. A Habitus of holotype. B Habitus of paratype. C Mouthparts of holotype. D Labels of holotype. E Metatarsus. F Mesotarsus. G Protarsus. Scale bars = 2 mm for A, B; 0.5mm for E, F, G." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7958991/files/figure.png" ;
